# Introduction

This plugin allows you to interact with the Mandrill API to manage your email templates and retrieve account information.

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/MtX9828RZkE?si=L8u_zOkTWvtafw63"></iframe>. 

# Configuration

Create an account on [Mailchimp platform](https://login.mailchimp.com/). Go to [Mandrill platform](https://mandrillapp.com/login/?referrer=%2F) and log in using Mailchimp. In settings you can create an API key which will allow you to use the Mailchimp API.

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

![mandrill_api_key](data:image/png;base64,)

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.   

# Create Configuration Data

In left side navigation go to data panel and choose "create". Then on blank option name your data and find data-format:

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

![CREATE_DATA](data:image/png;base64,)

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

Your configuration data should be a JSON object that includes the following field:

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

![DATA](data:image/png;base64,)

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.

# Available Methods

In Action section You can find available method's:

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

![actions](data:image/png;base64,)

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.   

## [**Mailchimp: Add Template**](https://mailchimp.com/developer/transactional/api/templates/add-template/)

This will create a new email template in Mandrill for sending transactional emails.

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

![LOGIC](data:image/png;base64,)

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

#### Expected Response

![RESPONSE](data:image/png;base64,)

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

- Also in Your Mandrill account You can find in Outbound - Templates your new created template from nocode-x.

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

![MANDRILL_RESPONSE](data:image/png;base64,)

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.   

## [**Mailchimp: Get User Info**](https://mailchimp.com/developer/transactional/api/users/get-user-info/)

This will fetch the user information of the currently authenticated user.

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

![LOGIC](data:image/png;base64,)

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.  

#### Expected Response

![RESPONSE](data:image/png;base64,)

<iframe width="0" height="5" src=""></iframe>.   

### [**Mailchimp: Get Template Info**](https://mailchimp.com/developer/transactional/api/templates/get-template-info/)

This will retrieve detailed information about a specific email template.

